title: For Sale:  Colt Model 1861 Navy (cartridge conversion)
postcontent:
This is an original Colt Model 1861 Navy Revolver fitted with a factory installed percussion-to-cartridge conversion - Richards-Mason type. These were converted during the mid to late 1870s from returns of various military and civilian 1861 Navy revolvers. (Civil War era) the conversion is post-Civil War from 1870s. They can be found in rim-fire (offset firing pin on hammer) or center-fire (centered firing pin on hammer). These were converted from .36 caliber percussion to .38 caliber cartridge; all of these revolvers - conversion or otherwise - retain the original .36 caliber markings. Both .36 and .38 calibers are low pressure black-powder loads and not intended for modern smokeless powder/loads. Of the earliest conversions +/- 2,250 were produced at the Colt factory and 2,000 of them were centerfire and the rest were rimfire. Meaning there should only be around 250 of these around.

I have seen these sell between 5,000 - 15,000 dollars but I am looking for a quick sale. 

I have lots of pictures if you want to see more. Or just meet up with me and look at it.

title: For Sale:  1895 Nagant revolver with ammo 1945 MUST SEE!
postcontent:
Up for sale here: is a russian 1895 nagant revolver, 7.62x38r caliber made by ishevsk in 1945.
What makes this revolver worth the extra is the fact that it was unissued, and manufactured in 1945, the last year of production for nagant revolvers. During ww2 hundreds of thousands were made, but only several thousand in 1945, it was thought that they would be needed against hitler, but the war ended before they could go into service. This revolver is in excellent condition, no finish wear, mirror shiny bore, the trigger pull is much smoother than most of the wartime production nagants. I am also including some surplus ammo 4 boxes are very rare as they are 1988 production (14 rounds in each box) the rest of the ammo was made in 1977. total of 175 rounds. The surplus ammo is not your run of the mill weak nagant ammo such as hotshot, ect, but is decently powerful. with the 77 production running about 1000fps and the 88 running 1300 or so.
I have fired around 200 rounds through this revolver, and it is very accurate as I was able to put strings of 7 into paper plates at 25 yards.
Pictures are available on request.
Absolutely NO trades will be accepted for this revolver - period.

title: For Sale:  SOLD-Forehand Antique 12 Gauge Shotgun
postcontent:
The Forehand Arms Co. ( originally as Forehand and Wadsworth) was in business from the early 1870's until acquired by Hopkins & Allen sometime after the middle 1890's. They manufactured only (I believe ) low cost trade guns. There is probably no longer any serial number histroy available to determine exact age. In order to determine value the condition of the firearm has to be known. My guess, though, is that unless it is in very good condition the value is such that it would best be used as a decoration in the den. As you more than likely have read in my previous responses, refrain from shooting the decarbonized steel gun. Same was designed for low pressure loads of black-powder. title: For Sale:  IZH Baikal Drozd - FULL Auto BB Gun / Russian made 1200 rounds per minute
postcontent:
For Sale ~ BB Gun Enthusiasts read ~~

As of 10/14/2012 - still for sale.  I've been answering quite a few emails about this gun ~ if you write me please allow me a day to respond back - the emails are lagging for some reason.  I'll answer you back asap.

The IZH Baikal Drozd imported by EAA is an awesome bb machine gun. This gun offers a select fire system like those offered on police and military weapons. One switch controls the rate of fire (ROF) with settings for 1, 3, or 6 round bursts. Meaning that each time you pull the trigger either 1, 3, or 6 bb's are fired simultaneously. The second switch controls how fast those rounds are actually fired as rounds per minute (RPM) with settings for 300, 450, and 600 rounds per minute.

Modified chip to allow full auto @ 1200 rounds per minute (Same as MP5). This means that as long as you hold down the trigger the IZH Drozd will keep firing. Other Drozd accessories include replacing the stock 12g CO2 powerlets with paint ball style tanks for CO2 and high pressure air (HPA). 

Aftermarket Drozd barrel which will increase your muzzle velocity and accuracy.

Comes stock from the factory with a removable and adjustable butt stock as well as a scope mount for accessories such as a red dot scope. The Drozd bb gun is a bb submachine gun, meaning that it is slightly larger than a bb pistol but smaller than a bb rifle. When you first pick it up you realize that the Drozd is not a toy and is indeed a serious piece of hardware for air gun enthusiasts.

Comes with Red/Green Dot Scope - Hi speed loader - HPA hose

Items:
IZH Drozd BB Gun
Red/Green Dot Scope
Hi Speed Loader
HPA Hose
Extended Barrel to increase accuracy and distance
